<h1>Steven Cravis</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="https://stevencravis.com/now">stevencravis.com/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
San Francisco
CA
United States
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Pianist | Composer | Producer of solo piano, ambient electronic, cinematic and pop music.
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
The most significant thing that could happen with my music on a broad scale is for it to help people feel whole, reduce stress and contribute to peace.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
I'm driven to write and share music with the world, because I believe it's a unique expression that is a necessary part of the world's and universe's combined story.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
I love each day's miracles, and I welcome more. The more we open ourselves to be aware of miracles, acknowledge each one, big or small, the more miracles we get to witness.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
“Super Brain” - by Rudy Tanzi and Deepak Chopra <<a href="http://www.amazon.com/Super-Brain-Unleashing-Explosive-Well-Being/dp/0307956830>">http://www.amazon.com/Super-Brain-Unleashing-Explosive-Well-Being/dp/0307956830></a>
</p>

